    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix ESM Status message encoding for cross-platform compatibility\n\n### Summary\nThe ESM Status message generation in the UE NAS stack produces malformed protocol messages on big-endian architectures due to inconsistent bitfield layout between union members. When the gNB processes these ESM Status messages, it fails to decode the EPS bearer identity and protocol discriminator fields correctly, causing premature connection release during initial attach procedures.\n\nThe issue manifests as UEs unable to establish default bearers when connecting to 5G networks, with the gNB logging \"Invalid EPS bearer identity\" errors. Memory dumps of the received ESM Status show the protocol discriminator and EPS bearer identity fields transposed compared to little-endian captures.\n\nRoot cause was the `esm_status_msg` structure lacking the endianness-aware bitfield definitions present in `esm_msg_header_t`, causing the `ESM_msg` union to interpret the same memory differently depending on which member was accessed.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/ESM/MSG/EsmStatus.h`: Added conditional compilation directives for `__LITTLE_ENDIAN_BITFIELD` and `__BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD` to ensure consistent bitfield ordering across architectures. Added `__attribute__((__packed__))` for alignment consistency.\n\n"
}